<br>
i get sick of these arguements.<br>
<br>
&quot;necros get a pet at level 1, therefore our pets should be better&quot;<br>
&quot;eot costs 20k and is rare, therefore it should be similiar strength to your epic&quot;<br>
&quot;eot requires 2 bone chips and dot therefore should be stronger than mage pets which use only malachite&quot;<br>
<br>
so on, so fourth.<br>
<br>
these baseless, silly conclusions are based upon faulty logic.<br>
<br>
sure, assuming all other things equal, something one class has with more draw backs should be better than something another class has with less drawbacks.<br>
<br>
the thing is all things <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  arent</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> equal, all classes have inherent strengths and weaknesses. people who fall back on those arguements overlook (perhaps selectively) this fact.<br>
<br>
magicians give up <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  alot</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to have a pet which can function almost like a make shift second character. no other class made the types of sacrifices we did. just because someone elses pet costs 100 more mana, or 10pp more than ours, doesnt even come close to compensating for a lack of any way to heal ourselves or mitigate damage aside from our pet.<br>
no other class, i repeat NOT ONE other class has zero way of healing themselves, or mitigating damage except mages.<br>
<br>
if eot costs alot of mana, and is rare, and uses a dot, ect ect, i fully agree compaired to other <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  necro</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> pets, it should be much stronger.<br>
<br>
... just dont expect it to compair to the sum abilities of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> equal rank (i.e. greater vocerate or higher) mage pet.<br>
